# Manual EFT Payment Approval System - Complete

We successfully built the requested EFT payment pipeline directly into the application. This setup allows students to directly upload their Proof of Payment document and gives you a single pane of glass to verify and approve their subscriptions.

## 1. The Student File Upload Pipeline
We created `EftUploadModal.jsx`. 
- Whenever a student clicks a locked Grade card in the `CurriculumHelper`, the screen now displays a beautiful popup instead of silently failing. 
- It shows them the two payment plans (R150 / R1,600) and displays a Unique Reference (based on their Email or UID) to use.
- When they select a file, it seamlessly uploads it to Firebase Storage in a new `proofs_of_payment` bucket and submits a record to the `pending_payments` Firestore database.

## 2. Administrator Dashboard Integration
We completely wired up a new "EFT Approvals" management sub-page for you.
- Navigate to your built-in `AdminView` (via the main header toggle).
- Click the new **EFT Approvals** card. 
- You will see a chronological queue of uploaded payments separated into Pending, Approved, and Rejected tabs.
- When scanning the list, you can click "View POP" to inspect the PDF or image they uploaded against your bank statement.
- **Approving**: You have two massive Action buttons: `1 Mo` or `12 Mo`. Clicking one instantly recalculates the new 31 or 365-day expiry period, upgrades the user's database entry, and unlocks the student's access.

> [!TIP]
> ### How to Test Your Pipeline
> 1. Launch the dev server and log in as a **Student** with an expired/free account.
> 2. Click a locked Grade card to trigger the modal.
> 3. Upload a dummy image representing a payment slip.
> 4. Log out and switch (or toggle if you are SuperAdmin) to your **Admin View**.
> 5. Open **EFT Approvals**, locate the mock payment, click **View POP**, and then click **1 Mo** to approve it!

